article.description: — Drew Lowder had 18 points to lead five Eastern Michigan players in double figures as the Eagles beat Akron 71-59 on Saturday.
article.headline: Five Eastern Michigan players in double figures in 71-59 win
article.linkText: Five Eastern Michigan players in double figures in 71-59 win
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. -- — Drew Lowder had 18 points to lead five Eastern Michigan players in double figures as the Eagles beat Akron 71-59 on Saturday. Yeikson Montero added 14 points for the Eagles (3-3, 1-2 Mid-American). Bryce McBride, Noah Morgan and Ty Groce had 10 points each. Montero also had six rebounds. Loren Cristian Jackson had 10 points for the Zips (4-2, 2-1) as did Maishe Dailey. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
